[The report above does not mention which hantavirus was responsible for this or earlier cases in Uruguay. Although not mentioned specifically, the infections, and certainly the deaths, will have resulted from hantavirus pulmonary syndrome (HPS). Central Plata hantavirus could be the etiological agent responsible for these HPS cases. Its rodent host is the yellow pygmy rice rat, _Oligoryzomys flavescens_, complex of rodents. This rodent reservoir host sheds the virus in its saliva, urine and feces, contaminating the environment in which it lives and breeds.

An image of this rodent can be accessed at http://www.reservacostanera.com.ar/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/colillargo.jpg.

This report was brought to our attention by Kathryn Soderholm <kathryn.soderholm@gmail.com>, whom we thank. - Mod.TY


A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5073021,28995.]
